Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.60,0:00:10.99,italics,nar,0000,0000,0000,,It appeared as though humanity \Nwould be destroyed by the demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.93,0:00:19.20,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,But a single mage saved them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.34,0:00:31.51,italics,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,He was called the Wizard King,\Nand he became a legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.67,0:00:40.87,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,The Eye of the Midnight Sun \Nis led by a man named Licht,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.87,0:00:44.53,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,who owns a four-leaf grimoire.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.53,0:00:47.68,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,They are a terrorist group he formed \Nsix years ago, and they hold
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.68,0:00:49.80,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,a grudge against the Clover Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.41,0:00:53.32,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,They have about fifty mages who are members.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.32,0:00:55.20,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Among them are their leader, Licht,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.20,0:00:59.01,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,as well as the three they call the \NThird Eye: Raia, Vetto, and Fana.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.01,0:01:02.03,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,They are much stronger \Nthan the other members.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.03,0:01:06.47,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,They all hold a strong grudge \Nagainst the Clover Kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.47,0:01:09.05,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,and they use that to justify \Ntheir terrorist attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.05,0:01:12.96,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Their endgame is to have an \Nindependent country of their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.35,0:01:15.30,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,That about covers everything, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.17,0:01:17.20,main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.20,0:01:20.68,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,And this is the most important \Nbit of information...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.97,0:01:25.30,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I've learned that there \Nis a traitor among you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.30,0:01:27.56,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,who is working with the \NEye of the Midnight Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.90,0:01:31.23,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Among the c-c-captains?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.90,0:01:33.90,italics,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.90,0:01:35.40,italics,Charlotte,0000,0000,0000,,Who could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.21,0:01:47.41,italics,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Because of you, Captain Fuegoleon was...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.41,0:01:50.92,italics,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Why?! Why would you betray us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.20,0:02:07.85,Ep Title,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Three-Leaf Salute
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.56,0:03:24.15,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Now, would you kindly tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.15,0:03:29.93,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,which one of these captains is the traitor \Nwho aided the Eye of the Midnight Sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.37,0:03:34.52,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me their name.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.94,0:03:37.16,main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.57,0:03:40.74,main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,The captain of the Purple Orcas,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.17,0:03:43.01,main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Gueldre Poizot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.21,0:03:47.28,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible! What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.75,0:03:51.56,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,Th-They're terrorists that \Nattacked our beloved nation!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.56,0:03:54.70,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,You'd actually believe what they're saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.70,0:03:58.17,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,As if I would ever betray the Clover Kingdom!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.17,0:04:00.09,main,Charlotte,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather not say this,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.33,0:04:04.65,main,Charlotte,0000,0000,0000,,but I've heard a few dark rumors about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.65,0:04:08.43,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just a few. We've heard many.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.43,0:04:10.39,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.33,0:04:15.54,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, I've heard \Nplenty of rumors like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.53,0:04:19.21,main,Charlotte,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, they weren't all false.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.67,0:04:24.65,main,Jack,0000,0000,0000,,I knew you were probably up to \Nsomething sketchy, but this is just...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.65,0:04:28.28,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be ridiculous! Th-This \Nmust be some kind of mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.28,0:04:32.79,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,I know! They're trying \Nto frame me as a traitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.79,0:04:36.96,main,Marx,0000,0000,0000,,They're only telling me what \Nthey know, plain and simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.21,0:04:40.78,main,Marx,0000,0000,0000,,Information obtained with \Nmy memory exchange magic
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.78,0:04:41.67,main,Marx,0000,0000,0000,,is absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.79,0:04:44.26,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,You heard him, Hard Ham.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.26,0:04:45.97,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.97,0:04:48.12,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Just calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.12,0:04:54.39,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Why not just let the guy with the \Nbowl cut look at your memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.39,0:04:57.40,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,If you're really a clean ham, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.40,0:05:00.49,main,Marx,0000,0000,0000,,I agree with everything other \Nthan what you called me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.49,0:05:03.49,main,Marx,0000,0000,0000,,If you're truly innocent, you should.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.49,0:05:05.78,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.78,0:05:08.04,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,What? Are you embarrassed?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.04,0:05:09.73,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,You a teenage boy or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.73,0:05:11.49,main,Charlotte,0000,0000,0000,,You're behaving shamefully, Gueldre.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.49,0:05:15.62,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,You will pay for betraying \Nthe kingdom with your death.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.62,0:05:18.30,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,So it really is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.30,0:05:21.42,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Because of you, Captain Fuegoleon was...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.08,0:05:25.42,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,No! This is some sort of trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.42,0:05:29.09,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,I'll clear my name! \NThis is a strategic retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.53,0:05:33.52,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,Transparency Creation Magic: \NInvisible Great Mage!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.15,0:05:39.27,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,He disappeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.80,0:05:41.39,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,He's actually trying to get away?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.39,0:05:43.53,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Well, this just got real.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.26,0:05:46.57,main,Charlotte,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't good. His transparency magic
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.57,0:05:50.20,main,Charlotte,0000,0000,0000,,makes him vanish for a set amount of time, \Nand all spells will go right through him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.67,0:05:55.50,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning while he's invisible, \Nour attacks won't do a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.50,0:05:58.21,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,What?! But that makes him invincible!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.21,0:06:02.59,italics,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,Transparency Creation Magic:\NInvisible Troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.25,0:06:06.34,italics,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,Hold them back for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.89,0:06:16.10,main,Charlotte,0000,0000,0000,,We can't just let him get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.73,0:06:25.88,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,Dorothy, this is no time to be sleeping!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.65,0:06:33.20,main,Jack,0000,0000,0000,,What are we going to do? We can't \Ncatch him if we can't see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.32,0:06:36.41,main,William,0000,0000,0000,,Yami.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.95,0:06:38.46,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.87,0:06:44.35,italics,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going to get caught \Nby the likes of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.35,0:06:46.41,italics,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,My magic is invincible!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.41,0:06:50.51,italics,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,I used this power to claw my way up to \Nthe position of Magic Knights Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.84,0:06:55.80,italics,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,Then I accumulated a fortune through \Nbusiness and became a wealthy merchant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.80,0:07:00.34,italics,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,I am a great mage who has \Nboth wealth and power!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.43,0:07:06.48,italics,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let it end here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.36,0:07:12.76,italics,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,I will rise again and again with this \Nmagic and my business talent!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.49,0:07:16.91,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,You're right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.39,0:07:19.25,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.65,0:07:25.24,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You shouldn't have been able to see me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.24,0:07:28.76,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,How?! How were you able to attack me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.17,0:07:35.21,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Hard Ham is able to hide his \Nmagical powers, but not his ki.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.21,0:07:40.27,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,And since the anti-magic sword \Nisn't magical, it'll work against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.82,0:07:47.02,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like an anti-magic kid who can read \Nki ended up being his natural enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.65,0:07:52.83,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,Don't mock me! I'm a captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.83,0:07:55.41,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,You magicless peasant!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.57,0:08:10.97,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,You look better when you're \Ngroveling on the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.97,0:08:12.13,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.99,0:08:15.30,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not letting you get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.30,0:08:18.03,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,The Magic Knights Captains \Nthat I admire so much
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.03,0:08:20.23,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,wouldn't run away over something like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.82,0:08:24.48,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. If you want to die that badly...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.48,0:08:27.11,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,I shall grant your wish for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.90,0:08:30.48,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Poizot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.61,0:08:35.07,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,Hold still a sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.00,0:09:02.14,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,Picture Magic: Spring of Restriction.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.15,0:09:09.08,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes, Mr. Poizot, you're\Na picture-perfect fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.08,0:09:10.11,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll call this...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.48,0:09:12.48,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Drowning Captain{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.48,0:09:13.36,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.17,0:09:15.90,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,What is this magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.81,0:09:22.12,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,Rill, how dare you go easy on him?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.12,0:09:24.71,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I mean, if I hadn't done that,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.08,0:09:28.12,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,this building would've been destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.12,0:09:31.78,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,His magic allows all magic \Nto pass through him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.78,0:09:34.92,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, we can simply \Nattack using physical objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.41,0:09:39.43,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,We'll just have some commoners \Nrebuild the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.49,0:09:44.43,main,Jack,0000,0000,0000,,I lost the chance to let loose on a captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.43,0:09:48.44,main,Jack,0000,0000,0000,,The guy resembles a ham exactly, \Nso he would've been perfect to slice up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.79,0:09:53.97,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,We're Magic Knight Captains. \NWe can't just sit around and space out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.97,0:09:56.18,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,We have to at least strike a pose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.28,0:09:59.70,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Are you still asleep?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.70,0:10:01.93,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, you still managed to keep up...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.93,0:10:04.18,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,You sure are reliable for \Nsomeone who's always asleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.70,0:10:09.34,main,Charlotte,0000,0000,0000,,Running away, even though \Nyou're a man. How pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.34,0:10:12.09,main,Charlotte,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you weren't a traitor, \Nyou'd still be a failure as a captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.77,0:10:16.23,italics,Charlotte,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Why is Yami only paying \Nattention to Dorothy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.23,0:10:18.59,italics,Charlotte,0000,0000,0000,,Does he like women like her?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.59,0:10:21.60,main,William,0000,0000,0000,,Friends, I believe that's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.15,0:10:25.85,main,William,0000,0000,0000,,Someone may be controlling him with magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.85,0:10:30.48,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, I'm glad I said that \Nwhen everyone was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.48,0:10:33.48,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I can't tone down my magic, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.83,0:10:36.17,italics,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,These people are insane!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.17,0:10:39.99,italics,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,These are the best Magic Knights... \Nthe best in the country?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.40,0:10:42.99,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You were amazing earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.33,0:10:45.56,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know where Mr. Poizot was?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.56,0:10:47.62,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,How'd you undo his transparency magic?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.62,0:10:49.41,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,U-Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.08,0:10:53.13,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,Well, whatever. I'm Rill,\Nand I'm nineteen! Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.13,0:10:57.29,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm Asta, and I'm fifteen. \NWait, you're nineteen and a captain?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.29,0:11:02.09,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, so you're younger than me!\NHey, Asta, be my friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.49,0:11:04.89,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, with a captain? Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.89,0:11:06.10,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Well, sure! Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.10,0:11:08.38,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,Yay! Just between you and me,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.38,0:11:13.10,main,Rill,0000,0000,0000,,everyone here's way older than me, so it's \Nbeen rough having to tiptoe around them!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.10,0:11:17.20,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,I see! And they're all weirdos, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.20,0:11:19.44,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you jerks. I can hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.44,0:11:22.45,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Also, {\i1}you're{\i0} the weirdos here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.77,0:11:24.87,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.87,0:11:27.95,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I have some questions for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.31,0:11:29.87,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Gueldre.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.31,0:11:41.88,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Gueldre, everything you've \Nsaid so far is true?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.88,0:11:43.34,main,Gueldre,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.15,0:11:46.68,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Man, that's quite the list.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.68,0:11:48.96,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Abusing his own squad members,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.96,0:11:51.48,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,embezzling funds, selling national \Ntreasure-class magic items
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.48,0:11:52.75,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,on the black market...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.75,0:11:55.67,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,And smuggling dangerous magic \Npotions from other countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.67,0:11:58.07,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,He's already pitch-black \Nbefore even being a traitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.48,0:12:02.33,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,He might be a good fit for the Black Bulls.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.33,0:12:05.67,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, becoming a burnt-black \Nham sounds better for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.17,0:12:08.70,main,Jack,0000,0000,0000,,What are you even going on about?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.70,0:12:12.08,main,Charlotte,0000,0000,0000,,So this is why he didn't want \Nhis memory read with magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.77,0:12:16.87,main,Charlotte,0000,0000,0000,,Most important of all... \NKidnapping barrier mages.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.87,0:12:20.21,main,Charlotte,0000,0000,0000,,That's direct cooperation with \Nthe Eye of the Midnight Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.21,0:12:24.08,main,Charlotte,0000,0000,0000,,That's solid proof of how they managed \Nto infiltrate the royal capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.08,0:12:28.14,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,He was dazzled by rare magic items and \Nmade a deal with those terrorists.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.14,0:12:29.39,main,Nozel,0000,0000,0000,,What a fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.33,0:12:35.23,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Well, unfortunately,\Nhe's always been like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.23,0:12:40.73,main,Marx,0000,0000,0000,,The Eye of the Midnight Sun has probably \Nkilled the kidnapped barrier mages already.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.45,0:12:44.49,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,This is an unparalleled blunder.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.17,0:12:47.76,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,He was a Magic Knight,\Ncharged with protecting our citizens,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.76,0:12:49.99,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,yet he sold them out instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.45,0:12:52.93,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,In order to keep the citizens \Nfrom growing uneasy,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.93,0:12:55.37,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,we won't make this a public matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.37,0:12:57.67,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,But to ensure that this never happens again,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.67,0:13:02.16,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,check all of your squad members to make \Nsure no one has ties to the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.16,0:13:03.34,main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.23,0:13:10.47,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.03,0:13:16.37,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a pretty decent actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.37,0:13:20.11,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,No one can see through my \Ncopy transformation magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.11,0:13:23.57,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,So which one of them was actually me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.57,0:13:27.49,main,Raia,0000,0000,0000,,Now nobody's going to be \Nsuspicious for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.85,0:13:39.17,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for making you two stay behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.81,0:13:45.15,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,It's sad... being betrayed by \Ncomrades who fought alongside me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.09,0:13:48.65,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I sprinted at full speed to get where I am,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.07,0:13:52.91,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,but as a result, I may have \Nmade a lot of mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.49,0:13:56.18,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the reason you had us stay behind,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.18,0:14:00.02,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,you picked the wrong guys, Julius.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.02,0:14:02.94,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,To tell you the truth, \Nwhen we were interrogating
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.94,0:14:04.76,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,the two Eye of the Midnight Sun members,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.76,0:14:05.99,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,they told us one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.45,0:14:09.78,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Asta, do you remember the stone \Ntablet back at their hideout
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.78,0:14:13.16,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,when you were taken by them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.57,0:14:14.74,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,That thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.74,0:14:19.17,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,They call the stones that were \Nset into it "magic stones."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.17,0:14:22.67,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,They believe that if they \Ncollect all of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.67,0:14:24.75,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,they will be reborn into their true forms,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.75,0:14:27.97,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,which are linked closely to mana, \Nand gain enormous power.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.31,0:14:30.17,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently they also went after Fuegoleon
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.17,0:14:33.47,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,because they wanted the \Nmagic stone that he had.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.15,0:14:37.36,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Reborn, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.36,0:14:40.48,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,You sure they didn't just read \None too many fantasy novels?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.48,0:14:45.31,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know whether that's true or not,\Nbut their obsession with it is real.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.31,0:14:48.12,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,We must not let them get the stones.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.12,0:14:49.83,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.83,0:14:51.87,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,There are three magic stones left.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.27,0:14:55.82,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,They know the location of one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.82,0:14:57.87,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah? And where's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.39,0:15:00.13,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,In a strong magic region...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.13,0:15:01.54,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,The Underwater Temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.37,0:15:04.95,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,A... strong magic region?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.50,0:15:06.88,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.55,0:15:09.76,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure you don't \Nneed this head anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.21,0:15:13.18,top,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Stop! I won't say any more! Please spare me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.76,0:15:11.66,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect. Let me crush it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.18,0:15:17.78,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Strong magic regions are, as the name \Nsuggests, regions with strong magic,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.78,0:15:22.14,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,where all sorts of magical phenomena \Noccur to prevent people from entering.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.14,0:15:25.23,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Of all the regions with strong magic,\Nthe Underwater Temple
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.23,0:15:27.75,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,is said to be especially dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.75,0:15:30.02,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,The dungeon you recently \Nconquered could be considered
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.02,0:15:32.24,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,a beginner's course in comparison.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.81,0:15:36.79,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,There's a place that's even \Nmore amazing than that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.29,0:15:41.08,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,So you want us to get there before \Nthe Eye of the Midnight Sun does
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.08,0:15:44.29,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,and snatch the magic stone or whatever?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.29,0:15:45.41,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.41,0:15:47.54,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,This is an important mission. \NThe best squad for the job
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.54,0:15:51.57,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,is the one with lots of members who aren't \Nrestricted by familial or social status...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.57,0:15:54.80,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Which means your Black Bulls, Yami.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.63,0:15:59.27,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,There may still be traitors \Namong the Magic Knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.01,0:16:01.67,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Will you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.51,0:16:07.27,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,You're the Wizard King. If that's \Nwhat you think, just give the order.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.75,0:16:13.43,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,As a captain, you're definitely right that \NI don't have anything holding me back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.55,0:16:20.76,flashback,villager 1,0000,0000,0000,,I hear he's not from this kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.76,0:16:25.03,flashback,villager 2,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently he's a castaway from some foreign \Ncountry who lives on the coast by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.03,0:16:27.29,flashback,Villager 3,0000,0000,0000,,He looks kinda dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.73,0:16:30.53,flashback,Villager 4,0000,0000,0000,,I wish he'd just leave the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.17,0:16:41.61,flashback,Guy 1,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious! Why does a \Nforeigner like him get a grimoire?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.03,0:16:44.47,flashback,Guy 2,0000,0000,0000,,I bet his magic's worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.47,0:16:47.52,flashback,Guy 3,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get rid of him with our magic later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.53,0:16:53.31,flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What's that magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.75,0:16:54.95,flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Scary...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.53,0:16:57.31,flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,How creepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.23,0:17:06.89,italics,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... Just because I got a grimoire, that\Ndoesn't change the fact that I'm a foreigner.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.89,0:17:10.61,italics,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have anything tying me down,\Nbut that also means I'll always be alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.61,0:17:12.23,italics,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Or so I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.61,0:17:16.34,flashback,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! That's dark magic, isn't it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.15,0:17:21.73,flashback,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing! I've never seen that before!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.73,0:17:24.39,flashback,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey, hey! Let me \Nget a better look at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.72,0:17:26.64,flashback,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,No. Who the heck are you, old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.64,0:17:30.52,flashback,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Old...? Oh, but I'm not suspicious at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.52,0:17:34.26,flashback,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just a Magic Knights Captain who \Nwas wandering around in disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.26,0:17:35.89,flashback,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,What's a Magic Knight?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.89,0:17:37.83,flashback,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? You don't know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.83,0:17:39.45,flashback,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.63,0:17:44.62,flashback,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Well, why not come see for yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.62,0:17:46.34,flashback,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you've got potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.34,0:17:47.14,flashback,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.14,0:17:49.86,flashback,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on! Don't be like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.86,0:17:50.66,flashback,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.66,0:17:51.88,flashback,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I'll treat you to dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.88,0:17:52.83,flashback,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.83,0:17:54.71,flashback,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I see. I guess that's not enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.71,0:17:56.29,flashback,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. You'll come?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.29,0:18:00.03,flashback,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go if you buy me dinner.\NI'll definitely go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.85,0:18:06.67,flashback,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,You sure are interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.41,0:18:10.97,italics,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I've been stuck with you ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.39,0:18:23.69,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just going to use my power \Nto prove it, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.69,0:18:25.95,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,To prove that you've made no mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.69,0:18:30.08,italics,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Yami's actually saluting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.61,0:18:32.23,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you, Yami.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.23,0:18:33.78,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,And you, Asta...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.78,0:18:35.13,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.41,0:18:40.27,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,It's a strange coincidence \Nthat you joined Yami's squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.27,0:18:42.80,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,Strong magic regions have \Nstrong mana force fields
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.80,0:18:45.14,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,around them that prevent \Noutsiders from getting in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.14,0:18:48.60,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt anyone would be able to \Nget in without your anti-magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.15,0:18:52.28,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,And your experience fighting \Nwith the Eye of the Midnight Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.28,0:18:53.65,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,is bound to be very useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.05,0:18:55.61,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.21,0:18:57.43,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.95,0:19:05.39,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,I got too excited and \Nknocked the air out of myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.89,0:19:06.55,top,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen someone \Nself-destruct from saluting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.77,0:19:11.17,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,I can definitely tell that you chose him,\Nconsidering how interesting he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.15,0:19:14.27,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,You were stiff as a board back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.27,0:19:16.69,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,I guess clowns can get nervous, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.69,0:19:19.42,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you calling a clown, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.81,0:19:24.16,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,It's just... I've never had someone who I \Nthought was amazing, like the Wizard King,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.16,0:19:26.68,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,expect anything from me before.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.28,0:19:31.19,flashback,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,Joining the Magic Knights when \Nyou can't even use magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.19,0:19:33.19,flashback,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.19,0:19:37.67,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, no one's ever really expected \Nanything from me to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.32,0:19:39.32,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.83,0:19:43.81,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,I let you join the Black Bulls \Nbecause I thought you could do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.89,0:19:46.83,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Work your butt off.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.31,0:19:50.41,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.83,0:19:55.01,main,All,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.87,0:19:58.22,main,Magna,0000,0000,0000,,The beach!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.22,0:20:00.58,main,Magna,0000,0000,0000,,Men bring to mind the beach! \NThe beach brings to mind men!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.58,0:20:02.64,main,Magna,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting all excited for no good reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.64,0:20:06.14,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Come to think of it, I've \Nnever even seen the ocean before!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.14,0:20:07.89,main,Magna,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't either, Shrimpsta!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.28,0:20:37.11,top,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Beach! Beach! Beach! Beach! Beach! Beach!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.31,0:20:15.17,main,Vanessa,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing better than enjoying \Na cold one under the blazing sun!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.86,0:20:17.56,main,Finral,0000,0000,0000,,Shake, shake, let's shake!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.56,0:20:22.22,main,Finral,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make some original drinks and flirt \Nwith some hotties in swimsuits on the beach!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.22,0:20:23.20,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,S-Swimsuits?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.59,0:20:24.86,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.86,0:20:29.55,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,If I go to the beach, I-I-I-I'll \Nhave to wear a swimsuit, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.33,0:20:34.49,main,Charmy,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Shrimp, Mr. Crab, and all the \Nmany other varieties of seafood,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.49,0:20:37.11,main,Charmy,0000,0000,0000,,I can't wait to grill you \Nall up on the beach...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.11,0:20:39.80,main,Gordon,0000,0000,0000,,I hope we all get to put sunscreen \Non each other at the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.65,0:20:42.67,main,Gauche,0000,0000,0000,,Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.34,0:20:46.10,main,Gauche,0000,0000,0000,,Captain, what should I get for Marie?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.10,0:20:48.65,main,Luck,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, sharks are strong, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.65,0:20:50.52,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,I hope the sharks eat you both.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.52,0:20:53.51,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,S-Swimsuit... Swimsuit...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.51,0:20:55.44,main,Vanessa,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't have one,\Nyou can borrow one of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.02,0:20:59.27,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Beach! Beach! Bea—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.82,0:21:01.28,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.57,0:21:08.83,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,We're not going for leisure! \NWe're going for work!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.08,0:21:10.62,main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.07,0:21:13.15,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,The Underwater Temple, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.15,0:21:15.29,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what it's like...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.89,0:22:56.43,sign_33083_276_Petit_Clover_,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,520)}Pe{\c&H3BC020&}t{\c&HE2AF0F&}i{\c&H3BC020&}t C{\c&HE2AF0F&}l{\c&H3BC020&}o{\c&H0E42D4&}ve{\c&H3BC020&}r
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.97,0:22:55.97,main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Petit Clover!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.93,0:22:59.94,sign_33188_278_The_Mystery_of_t,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(520,1)}Game Tournament
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.63,0:22:59.41,main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Game Tournament.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.94,0:23:02.19,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,This is so cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.19,0:23:07.03,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,To think your magic can let us play games \Nlike this... You're amazing, Mr. Bowlcut!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.03,0:23:09.15,main,Marx,0000,0000,0000,,This is called memory amusement magic,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.15,0:23:11.51,main,Marx,0000,0000,0000,,and it allows you to battle with characters
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.51,0:23:13.20,main,Marx,0000,0000,0000,,you've created from your memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.20,0:23:15.45,main,Marx,0000,0000,0000,,And my name is Marx—
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.14,0:23:18.08,top,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! The captain was super \Nstrong when he was young!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.46,0:23:21.25,main,Julius,0000,0000,0000,,How nostalgic. It's Yami \Nwhen I first met him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.25,0:23:23.59,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,You're no match for me, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.59,0:23:25.60,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet! I'm not done yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.60,0:23:27.42,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Go right! Right! Counterattack!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.42,0:23:29.35,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,Now left!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.35,0:23:31.47,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.91,0:23:34.68,main,Yami,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we have a real battle \Ninstead of one in a game?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.97,0:23:34.68,top,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,I'll die!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.68,0:23:37.95,main,Asta,0000,0000,0000,,It'll seriously be game over!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.33,0:23:42.54,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What should I do? If we're going \Nto the beach, I'll need a swimsuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.54,0:23:44.27,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,I need to buy a new one!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.27,0:23:46.73,main,Noelle,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what kind Asta likes...
